column1: #List of genes with at least 1 signal of positive selection across the 6792 samples.

##ALL_Leu,ALL_Mem,ALL_NewS,AST_NewS,AST_SJ,BCell_Lymp,BLCA_TCGA,BRCA_BC,BRCA_Broad,BRCA_JH,BRCA_Sanger,BRCA_TCGA,BRCA_WU,CLL_Broad,CLL_HC,COADREAD_TCGA,CO_JH,ESO_DFCI,GAST_Pfizer,GBM_JH,GBM_TCGA,HNSC_Broad,HNSC_TCGA,KIRC_TCGA,LAML_TCGA,LGG_TCGA,LIV_FR,LIV_ICGC,LUAD_TCGA,LUNG_TSP,LUSC_TCGA,MED_NewS,Myeloma_NewS,NBM_Broad,NSCLC_Wisc,OV_TCGA,PAAD_JH,PAAD_OICR,PAAD_QCMG,POOLED,PRAD_TCGA,PedBrain,SCLC_Cologne,SCLC_JH,SKCM_Broad,SKCM_TCGA,STAD_TCGA,THCA_TCGA,UCEC_TCGA = = projects where gene exhibits signals of positive selection. R: Gene exhibiting significant recurrence of mutations (detected by MutSigCV) in the corresponding tumor type; F: Gene exhibiting significant FMbias (detected by OncodriveFM) in the corresponding tumor type; C: Gene exhibiting significant clustering (detected by OncodriveCLUST) in the corresponding tumor type.
##Pooled: Results of the analysis of all TCGA datasets together
##VariousSignals_geneCounts: Number of datasets where the driver gene exhibits at least two signals of positive selection
##OneSingleSignal_geneCounts: Number of datasets where the driver gene exhibits at least one signal of positive selection
##Recur_counts: Number of datasets where the driver gene exhibits significant mutational recurrence
##FM_counts: Number of datasets where the driver gene exhibits significant FMbias
##CLUST_counts: Number of datasets where the driver gene exhibits significant CLUSTbias
##CGC: The driver gene is in the CGC
##HCD_seed: The driver gene is either a two-signal gene or a one-signal-CGC gene
##driver gene_connected: The driver gene is connected through protein-protein or functional interactions to an HCD_seed driver gene.
##Where_detected: Indicates whether the driver gene was detected as such either in a single project, in the pooled TCGA cohort, or in both.
